sentences: Finne Jager (Dutch pronunciation: [ˈfɪnə ˈjaːɣər]; born 6 December 1984), commonly known as Phynn, is a Dutch trance and techno DJ and producer.
In 2000, Finne discovered his love for electronic dance music.
In the second half of 2004, Finne (now commonly known as Phynn) decided to make a record with his friend Bart Van Wissen, known as Fictivision.

As of today it remains one of his biggest and most well known records.
Finne was introduced to the 'big audience' as a closing act for Tiësto at the Heineken Music Hall in Amsterdam, on December 3, 2005, in front of an audience of over 5000 people.
One month later, Phynn was declared 'Future Hero' by Mixmag, a well known electronic dance music magazine.
In March 2007, Phynn reached a milestone in his career when he was asked to perform at the Main Stage of the world's biggest annual trance event Trance Energy, organized by Dutch event company ID&T.
The audience size at Trance Energy 2007 counted over 25,000 people.
In 2008, Phynn performed at Trance Energy again at the 'Future Stage'.
Phynn released his debut artist album in November 2008 on Black Hole Recordings.
Notable tracks from the album are 'Try Again feat, Tiff Lacey', 'Wait For A Moment feat.
Starfire At Night', 'Metamorphosis' and 'No More Mistakes feat Molly Bancroft'.
In 2009, Phynn released 'Spacewalk' on Black Hole Recordings.
The song was an instant success, and top DJ's like Markus Schulz played the record for many months after its initial release, and it was placed on many compilations worldwide.
Just like 'Spacewalk', 'Hello Love' was a big hit with fans around the world, leading Ferry Corsten to include it on his Once Upon A Night mixed compilation.
As a result of the success of 'Spacewalk' and 'Hello Love', world-famous DJ Markus Schulz approached Phynn in 2010 to do remixes for Coldharbour Recordings.
Statica - Deadly Nightshade', 'Rex Mundi - Opera of Northern Ocean', 'Hammer & Bennet - Language' and 'Markus Schulz - Rain'.
In June 2014, Phynn announced on his Facebook page that he will no longer be making Trance music, and that he is taking a new musical direction and will focus on Techno going forward.
